y them","kjv_def":"Daniel","pos":"proper locative noun, proper masculine noun","usage":"Dan(70x), variant(1x)"},"H1836":{"id":"H1836","lemma":"דֵּן","translit":"dên","pron":"dane","derivation":"(Aramaic) an orthographical variation of H1791 (דֵּךְ);","strongs_def":"this","kjv_def":"(afore-) time, [phrase] after this manner, here (-after), one...another, such, there(-fore), these, this (matter), [phrase] thus, where(-fore), which.","pos":"adverb, demonstrative pronoun","usage":"this(38x), these(3x), thus(2x), hereafter(1x), that(1x)"},"H1837":{"id":"H1837","lemma":"דַּנָּה","translit":"Dannâh","pron":"dan-naw'","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"Dannah, a place in Palestine","kjv_def":"Dannah.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Dannah(1x)"},"H1838":{"id":"H1838","lemma":"דִּנְהָבָה","translit":"Dinhâbâh","pron":"din-haw-baw'","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"Dinhabah, an Edomitish town","kjv_def":"Dinhaban."},"H1839":{"id":"H1839","lemma":"דָּנִי","translit":"Dânîy","pron":"daw-nee'","derivation":"patronymically from H1835 (דָּן);","strongs_def":"a Danite (often collectively) or descendants (or inhabitants) of Dan","kjv_def":"Danites, of Daniel","pos":"adjective","usage":"Danite(4x), Dan(1x)"},"H1840":{"id":"H1840","lemma":"דָנִיֵּאל","translit":"Dânîyêʼl","pron":"daw-nee-yale'","derivation":"in Ezekiel it is; דָּנִאֵל; from H1835 (דָּן) and H410 (אֵל); judge of God;","strongs_def":"Daniel or Danijel, the name of two Israelites","kjv_def":"Daniel.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Daniel(29x)"},"H1841":{"id":"H1841","lemma":"דָּנִיֵּאל","translit":"Dânîyêʼl","pron":"daw-nee-yale'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H1840 (דָנִיֵּאל);","strongs_def":"Danijel, the Hebrew prophet","kjv_def":"Daniel.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Daniel(52x)"},"H1842":{"id":"H1842","lemma":"דָּן יַעַן","translit":"Dân Yaʻan","pron":"dawn yah'-an","derivation":"from H1835 (דָּן) and (apparently) H3282 (יַעַן); judge of pu