ly from the same as H1865 (דְּרוֹר);","strongs_def":"properly, a pearl (from its sheen as rapidly turned); by analogy, pearl-stone, i.e. mother-of-pearl or alabaster","kjv_def":"[idiom] white.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"white(1x)"},"H1859":{"id":"H1859","lemma":"דָּר","translit":"dâr","pron":"dawr","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H1755 (דּוֹר);","strongs_def":"an age","kjv_def":"generation.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"generation(4x)"},"H1860":{"id":"H1860","lemma":"דְּרָאוֹן","translit":"dᵉrâʼôwn","pron":"der-aw-one'","derivation":"or דֵּרָאוֹן; from an unused root (meaning to repulse);","strongs_def":"an object of aversion","kjv_def":"abhorring, contempt.","pos":"masculine noun"},"H1861":{"id":"H1861","lemma":"דׇּרְבוֹן","translit":"dorbôwn","pron":"dor-bone'","derivation":"(also dor-bawn'); of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"a goad","kjv_def":"goad.","pos":"masculine/feminine noun","usage":"goad(2x)"},"H1862":{"id":"H1862","lemma":"דַּרְדַּע","translit":"Dardaʻ","pron":"dar-dah'","derivation":"apparently from H1858 (דַּר) and H1843 (דֵּעַ); pearl of knowledge;","strongs_def":"Darda, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Darda."},"H1863":{"id":"H1863","lemma":"דַּרְדַּר","translit":"dardar","pron":"dar-dar'","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"a thorn","kjv_def":"thistle.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"thistle(2x)"},"H1864":{"id":"H1864","lemma":"דָּרוֹם","translit":"dârôwm","pron":"daw-rome'","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"the south; poet. the south wind","kjv_def":"south.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"south(17x)"},"H1865":{"id":"H1865","lemma":"דְּרוֹר","translit":"dᵉrôwr","pron":"der-ore'","derivation":"from an unused root (meaning to move rapidly);","strongs_def":"freedom; hence, spontaneity of outflow, and so clear","kjv_def":"liberty, pure.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"liberty(7x), pure(1x)"},"H1866":{"id":"H1866","lemma":"דְּרוֹר","translit":"dᵉrôwr","pron":"der-ore'","derivation":"the same as 